## Code conventions

**Bash:** `#!/usr/bin/env bash` → header block (Script Name, Description, Author, Created, Version) → bash version guard → `set -eo pipefail` → section dividers exactly 80 chars: `# ──[ Section Name ]──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────` → `trap '...' ERR` → `usage()` + case-based arg parsing → functions with `local` vars → main logic last. Always `printf` not `echo`. Status decorators: `BANNER[^]`, `PLUS[+]`, `COMPLETE[*]`, `FAILED[!]`, `LAMBDA[λ]` — yellow brackets, coloured inner symbol. `LAMBDA` uses sage green (#79be9a) — personal signature on the final entry line. Binary detection: `command -v`. Arch: `case "$(uname -m)"`. Shared utils in lib.sh — source it, don't copy-paste. Temp dirs: `mktemp -d` + `trap RETURN`.

**Python:** `#!/usr/bin/env python3` → triple-quoted module docstring (name, description, author) → `__version__` → section dividers exactly 88 chars: `# ──[ Section Name ]─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────` → imports grouped stdlib/third-party/internal each with a divider → type hints everywhere → one router per module (FastAPI). No comments that describe what — only why when non-obvious.

